  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nWhen validating a newly imported block, we do a `self.get_vm(uncle)` for every uncle of the block, but that will crash when the uncle has not been previously persisted to the DB. That happens because the `get_vm()` call will try to load the uncle's transactions from the DB and will crash with a KeyError when those are not found. This is a regression that has been introduced by #740 -- before that we didn't have the `self.get_vm(uncle)` call as we were using the imported block's VM to perform the uncle validation\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nNot sure\r\n",
